ovince (Puno Region)</ref>\n| prominence_m  =\n| prominence_ref=\n| location = [[Peru]]\n| range = [[Andes]], [[Cordillera Apolobamba|Apolobamba]] \n| map = Peru\n| range_coordinates = \n| map_caption = Location within Peru\n| label_position = right\n| map_size       = 200\n| coordinates   = {{coord|14|35|26|S|69|29|00|W|type:mountain_region:PE_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_ref= \n| type = \n| age = \n| last_eruption = \n| first_ascent = \n| easiest_route = \n}}\n'''Jorhuari''' or '''Ccorhuari''' (possibly from [[Aymara language|Aymara]] for [[mold]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aymara.ucb.edu.bo/html/diccionario/castellano%20aymara/am.html|title=Diccionario Biling\u00fce, Castellano - Aymara, 2002|last1=|first1=|last2=|first2=|date=|website=|publisher=F\u00e9lix Layme Pairumani|accessdate=December 17, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923181126/http://www.aymara.ucb.edu.bo/html/diccionario/castellano%20aymara/am.html|archive-date=September 23, 2015|url-status=dead}} (see: ''Moho'')</ref> is a mountain in the [[Cordillera Apolobamba|Apolobamba]] mountain range in the [[Andes]] of [[Peru]], about {{convert|5200|m|ft|0}} high. It is located in the [[Puno Region]], [[San Antonio de Putina Province|Putina Province]], [[Ananea District]], and in the [[Sandia Province]], [[Cuyocuyo District]]. It lies southwest of the mountain [[Wilaquta (Sandia)|Vilacota]].<ref name=escale/> \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Mountains of Puno Region]]\n[[Category:Mountains of Peru]]\n\n\n{{Puno-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Crouch, Swale", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toMold(link changed toMold (fungus)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jorhuari"}
